<paragraph id="EA2136CB366A181AFF71FE92FDAEE571" blockId="37.[177,631,256,276]" box="[177,631,256,276]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="CA8E11E5366A181AFF71FE92FDAEE571" box="[177,631,256,276]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">
<treatmentCitation id="6B3F10DA366A181AFF71FE92FDC7E571" author="SCHRANK F" box="[177,542,256,276]" page="653" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" year="1798">
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFF71FE92FDC7E571" authority="SCHRANK 1798: 653" authorityName="SCHRANK" authorityPageNumber="653" authorityYear="1798" box="[177,542,256,276]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verbasci">
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFF71FE92FE83E571" box="[177,346,256,276]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">Paederus verbasci</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8E0F4B3A366A181AFE9FFE92FDC7E571" author="SCHRANK F" box="[351,542,256,276]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" refId="ref36336" refString="SCHRANK F. von PAULA (1798): Fauna Boica. Durchgedachte Geschichte der in Baiern einheimischen und zahmen Thiere. Erster Band. - Nurnberg: Stein'sche Buchhandlung: xii + 720 pp." type="book" year="1798">SCHRANK 1798: 653</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
; 
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFDE7FE92FDAEE571" bold="true" box="[551,631,256,276]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">nov.syn.</emphasis>
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA2136CB366A181AFF71FEB7FD7BE618" blockId="37.[177,1085,293,637]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">
C o m m e n t: 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFEA5FEB7FD56E55C" authority="SCHRANK" authorityName="SCHRANK" authorityYear="1798" box="[357,655,293,315]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verbasci">
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFEA5FEB7FDFAE55E" box="[357,547,293,315]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">Paederus verbasci</emphasis>
SCHRANK
</taxonomicName>
, too, is listed as a nomen dubium in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFF34FED0FE8AE53D" box="[244,339,322,344]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFF34FED0FE8AE53D" box="[244,339,322,344]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">Paederus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="8E0F4B3A366A181AFEBCFED0FDF4E53D" author="SMETANA A" box="[380,557,322,344]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" pagination="579 - 698" refId="ref36443" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Subfamily Paederinae FLEMING, 1821, subfamily Staphylininae Latreille, 1802. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Stenstrup: Apollo Books: 579 - 698." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. The original description is contained in a work on Bavarian animals and based on an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus id="35258869366A181AFCC1FEF2FC84E510" box="[769,861,352,373]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">syntypes</typeStatus>
. The details indicated in this description (&quot;sattschwarz; der Rückenschild halbkugelförmig; das lezte Glied der vordern Fressspizen fadenförmig, das vorlezte keulenförmig.... unter den Blättern des Wollkrautes.... Lang 1 1/4. Die Flügeldecken gerundet, wie bey den Oelkäfern, vielleicht flügellos.... am lezten Ringe des Hinterleibes... einen Haarbüschel beiderseits&quot;) (
<bibRefCitation id="8E0F4B3A366A181AFF79FE60FE80E66D" author="SCHRANK F" box="[185,345,498,520]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" refId="ref36336" refString="SCHRANK F. von PAULA (1798): Fauna Boica. Durchgedachte Geschichte der in Baiern einheimischen und zahmen Thiere. Erster Band. - Nurnberg: Stein'sche Buchhandlung: xii + 720 pp." type="book" year="1798">SCHRANK 1798</bibRefCitation>
), are not easily interpreted. The name clearly does not refer to a species of 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFF12FD9DFEE8E640" box="[210,305,527,549]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFF12FD9DFEE8E640" box="[210,305,527,549]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">Paederus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but possibly one of 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFDE3FD9DFD56E640" authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1825" box="[547,655,527,549]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Omaliinae">Omaliinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFD5EFD9DFCC9E640" authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1821" box="[670,784,527,549]" class="Insecta" family="Oxytelinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oxytelinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFCE0FD9DFCA3E640" authorityName="W.S.MacLeay" authorityYear="1825" box="[800,890,527,549]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Steninae">Steninae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFC4AFD9DFBC1E640" authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1825" box="[906,1048,527,549]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tachyporinae">Tachyporinae</taxonomicName>
, or 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFF71FDBEFDCEE627" authority="(Aleochara, Autalia)" baseAuthorityName="Aleochara, Autalia" box="[177,535,556,578]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aleocharinae">
Aleocharinae (
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFE8AFDBEFE6AE627" box="[330,435,556,578]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">Aleochara</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFE03FDBEFDD4E627" box="[451,525,556,578]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">Autalia</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
, if it refers to a species of 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFCFCFDBEFC1EE627" box="[828,967,556,578]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Staphylinidae</taxonomicName>
at all. The only older name fairly in agreement with the description is that of 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFC99FDDBFBEFE63A" baseAuthorityName="GEOFFROY" baseAuthorityYear="1785" box="[857,1078,585,607]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Platystethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenarius">
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFC99FDDBFBEFE63A" box="[857,1078,585,607]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">Platystethus arenarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which 
<taxonomicName id="2D9E4D48366A181AFEE9FDFAFE42E618" authorityName="SCHRANK" authorityYear="1798" box="[297,411,615,637]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verbasci">
<emphasis id="D8EAEAD9366A181AFEE9FDFAFE42E618" box="[297,411,615,637]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1274">P. verbasci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is formally synonymised.
</paragraph>
